Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, has called on Nigerians to pray for leaders. The lawmaker also urged Christians to pray for the country to overcome the myriad of problems, especially insecurity. The Surulere representative advised them to imbibe the teachings of Jesus Christ. In his Christmas message, Gbajabiamila said periods like this call for sober reflection. “Nigerians, irrespective of where they come from, must work towards achieving the dreams of our founding fathers, who made a lot of sacrifices for us to be one”, he stressed. Noting that year 2020 came with the COVID-19 challenge, the Speaker said with prayers and observance of the established protocols, “the country shall overcome it in the end.” Gbaja wished all Nigerians happy celebrations and appealed for caution as they merry.